  "market_context": "EUR/USD chart showing a defined support zone between ~1.14140 and 1.14160, with multiple bounces, then a decisive break below that zone leading to a downside move and immediate retest of the broken support as resistance.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst highlighted that support acted as a zone (not a line), produced three clear bounces, then broke—triggering a strong downside move and a quick retest of the former support as resistance.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a gray-shaded support zone on the EUR/USD chart between approximately 1.14140 and 1.14160.",
    "Step 2: Pointed out three prior price approaches to that zone resulting in strong upward bounces (including one very strong bounce and a smaller test).",
    "Step 3: Noted the fourth approach resulted in a break below the support zone, confirming failure of the support level.",
    "Step 4: Observed that after the break, price quickly rallied back to retest the broken support level as resistance—a common market behavior."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Support and resistance are zones, not precise lines; repeated tests increase significance, but eventual breaks can trigger strong moves; broken support often becomes resistance on retest.",
